üìò ASSIGNMENT: PRODUCT MANAGEMENT REST API WITH EXPRESS.JS
============================================================

üéØ OBJECTIVE:
Create a RESTful API for managing products using Node.js and Express. 
This assignment will help you understand route handling, request methods, 
and basic data flow using Express.

------------------------------------------------------------
üõ†Ô∏è REQUIREMENTS:
------------------------------------------------------------

1Ô∏è‚É£ SETUP PROJECT
-------------------
- Initialize a Node.js project:
    > npm init -y

- Install Express:
    > npm install express

- Create a file named: 
    > server.js

- Write your Express app inside `server.js`.

2Ô∏è‚É£ DEFINE ROUTES
-------------------
Create the following API routes:

üîπ GET /products  
    ‚û§ Return a list of all products.  
    ‚û§ Use an in-memory array of product objects.

üîπ POST /products  
    ‚û§ Accept new product data in the body.  
    ‚û§ Required fields: name, price, category.  
    ‚û§ Log the received product data.

üîπ PUT /products/:id  
    ‚û§ Update a product with the given ID.  
    ‚û§ Log the ID and updated product data.

üîπ DELETE /products/:id  
    ‚û§ Delete a product with the given ID.  
    ‚û§ Return a confirmation message.

3Ô∏è‚É£ SAMPLE PRODUCT STRUCTURE
------------------------------
{
  id: 1,
  name: "Laptop",
  price: 49999,
  category: "Electronics"
}

4Ô∏è‚É£ MIDDLEWARE (BONUS)
------------------------
‚û§ Create a middleware to log each incoming request's method and URL.

Example:
    Incoming request: GET /products

5Ô∏è‚É£ TESTING
-------------
‚û§ Use Postman or curl to test all routes.  
‚û§ Create at least 3 product entries and perform all CRUD operations.

------------------------------------------------------------
üì§ SUBMISSION:
------------------------------------------------------------

- Submit your `server.js` file.
- Include screenshots or curl command results for testing.

------------------------------------------------------------
‚úÖ EXAMPLE CURL COMMANDS:
------------------------------------------------------------

‚û§ GET all products:
curl -X GET http://localhost:3000/products

‚û§ POST a new product:
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/products -d "name=Phone&price=9999&category=Electronics" -H "Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded"

‚û§ PUT to update a product:
curl -X PUT http://localhost:3000/products/1 -d "price=8999" -H "Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded"

‚û§ DELETE a product:
curl -X DELETE http://localhost:3000/products/1

